    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5870" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λούω, λοέω</span></b>  (cf. lavo), ipf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λοῦον, λὄ</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λόϝε</span>), aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λοῦς</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εν</span>), subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λούσῃ</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λόεσον,
            λούσατε</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λοἕσ̓σαι</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λοέσᾱσα</span>, mid. pres. inf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λούεσθαι, λοῦσθαι</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λοέσσομαι</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λοέσσατο, λούσαντο</span>, etc., pass. perf. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λελουμένος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bathe, wash</span>, mid.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bathe, get washed.</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 6.508</span></i>; fig., of the rising of
          Sirius, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λελουμένος Ὠκεανοῖο</span>, ‘after
          his bath in Ocean,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 5.6</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
